post_text: Based on decisions made yesterday by the The Colorado High School Activities Association (CHSAA) related to athletics and activities, the district is suspending all after school activities from March 13th-April 6th. On April 6, the district will re-evaluate the situation and make a decision regarding activities. This includes the league wrestling tournament tomorrow, the school dance tonight, Catch, track and soccer practices as well.

On April 6, the district will re-evaluate the situation and make a decision regarding activities. This includes the league wrestling tournament tomorrow, the school dance tonight, Catch, track and soccer practices as well.

post_text: Our 5th graders spent their Valentines Day engaged in our annual snow science adventure learn day on Reservoir Hill. post_text: Heart Day is coming up! Who We Play For will be returning this Friday February 14, for all 8th grade students! Please sign your student’s form they bring home or register online at the link below. Pagosa Springs Middle School cares about your child's heart health, so we are partnering with Who We Play For to screen students with and electrocardiogram (ECG). This procedure can detect issues in the heart that can be missed in standard physicals. The BEST part is it is FREE thanks to Pagosa Rotary and other generous donors. Qualified health professionals will screen Friday the 14th during PE or band class. Our goal is 100% participation! https://www.whoweplayfor.org/screening

All 5th & 6th grade Wolf Creek Ski Program paperwork is due Thursday, Jan. 9th. Parents, please encourage your child to participate in this amazing learning opportunity. Scholarships are available and all you have to do is write scholarship on the payment page. If you would rather your child not ski or snowboard, they can snowshoe or cross country ski for free using school district equipment. This is a great learning opportunity for your child to grow in their fitness, health and life experience. Please support us in offering this program by encouraging your child to participate.

Paperwork was sent home before break and/or you can access paperwork online at middle.mypagosaschools.com by clicking the Parent Tab or visit our office.

post_text:
Tdap Shot Required for all 6th Graders

All incoming 6th graders are required to have the Tdap (tetanus/diphtheria/pertussis) booster shot by the first day of school, September 3, 2019.

This shot is available at:
San Juan Basin Public Health (970-264-2409)
Pagosa Springs Medical Center (970-731-3700)
Pagosa Medical Group (970-372-0456)
Axis (970-264-2104)
Walmart (970-731-9017)
City Market (970-731-6006)

If you would rather sign an exemption to decline this shot, please do so before the first day of school. Exemption forms will be in the front office at the school.

If you have any questions, please call Julie August, Health Clerk, at 970-264-2256, or email jaugust@pagosa.k12.co.us.
